- Substitute the given solution into the left-hand side of the equation:

$$
\begin{pmatrix}
3x + y \\
-x + y
\end{pmatrix} = \begin{pmatrix}
3t - t + 1 \\
-t - t + 1
\end{pmatrix}e^{2t} = \begin{pmatrix}
2t + 1 \\
-2t + 1
\end{pmatrix}e^{2t}
$$

<marks>M1 A1</marks>

- Calculate the derivative of the given solution:

$$
\begin{pmatrix}
\dot{x} \\
\dot{y}
\end{pmatrix} = \begin{pmatrix}
e^{2t} + t(2e^{2t}) \\
-e^{2t} + (-t + 1)(2e^{2t})
\end{pmatrix} = \begin{pmatrix}
2t + 1 \\
-2t + 1
\end{pmatrix}e^{2t}
$$

<marks>M1 A1 A1</marks>

- Conclude that $\begin{pmatrix} x \\ y \end{pmatrix} = \begin{pmatrix} t \\ -t + 1 \end{pmatrix}e^{2t}$ is also a solution <marks>AG</marks>

